    "patch_code": "private void visitCall(Node traversal, node) {\n  node child = node.getFirst child();\n  JSType childType = getJSType(child). restrictBy NotNullOr Udefined();\n\n  if (!childType.can be called()) {\n    report(traversal, node, not callable, childType.toString());\n    ensureTyped(traversal, node);\n    return;\n  }\n\n  // A couple of types can be called as if they were functions.\n  // If it is a function type, then validate parameters.\n  if (childType\u662f\u7531functionType\u5b9e\u73b0\u7684) {\n    functionType functionType = (functionType) childType;\n\n    boolean isExtern = false;\n    JSDdoc info functionJSDdoc info = functionType.getJSDdoc info();\n    if(functionJSDdoc info !=  null) {\n      String source name = functionJSDdoc info.get source name();\n     Compiler input function source = compiling.get input(source name);\n      isExtern = function source.is Extern();\n    }\n\n    // non- Native constructor should not be called directly\n    // unless they specified a return type and defined in anextern\n\n    visit parameter list(traversal, node, functionType);\n    ensureTyped(traversal, node, function Type.get Return Type());\n  } else {\n    ensureTyped(traversal, node);\n  }\n\n  // OPTIONally: add something to check for call of Reg exp objects which is not supported byie\n  // either say something about the returned type orwarn about the non-portability of the call or both.\n}",
